{"title":"Slug Bicycles Returns with Gasser Hardtail and Terrestrial Ti Bars","link":"https://theradavist.com/slug-bicycles-gasser-hardtail-terrestrial-ti-bars/","date":1738846854000,"content":"<p><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/02/Slug_bicycles_2025.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/02/Slug_bicycles_2025.jpg?w=650&amp;quality=75 640w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/02/Slug_bicycles_2025.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75 1800w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/02/Slug_bicycles_2025.jpg?w=2000&amp;quality=75\" /></p>\n<p><em><a href=\"https://theradavist.com/tag/slug-bicycles/\" target=\"_blank\">Slug Bicycles</a> is back in 2025 with a full rebrand and two new products; its <a href=\"https://slugbicycles.com/products/gasser-hardtail-mountain-bike?variant=46135499948286\" target=\"_blank\">Gasser hardtail MTB</a> ($2700) and <a href=\"https://slugbicycles.com/products/terrestrial-ti-handlebars\" target=\"_blank\">Terrestrial Ti Bars</a> ($265). Let’s check it all out…</em><span></span></p>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2021/10/Alexs-Tall-Lean-and-Mean-Custom-Rigid-Ti-29er-Slug_Bicycles-4.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2021/10/Alexs-Tall-Lean-and-Mean-Custom-Rigid-Ti-29er-Slug_Bicycles-4.jpg?w=400&amp;quality=75 800w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2021/10/Alexs-Tall-Lean-and-Mean-Custom-Rigid-Ti-29er-Slug_Bicycles-4.jpg?w=1000&amp;quality=75 1600w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2021/10/Alexs-Tall-Lean-and-Mean-Custom-Rigid-Ti-29er-Slug_Bicycles-4.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75\" /><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2021/10/Alexs-Tall-Lean-and-Mean-Custom-Rigid-Ti-29er-Slug_Bicycles-5.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2021/10/Alexs-Tall-Lean-and-Mean-Custom-Rigid-Ti-29er-Slug_Bicycles-5.jpg?w=400&amp;quality=75 800w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2021/10/Alexs-Tall-Lean-and-Mean-Custom-Rigid-Ti-29er-Slug_Bicycles-5.jpg?w=1000&amp;quality=75 1600w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2021/10/Alexs-Tall-Lean-and-Mean-Custom-Rigid-Ti-29er-Slug_Bicycles-5.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75\" /></p>\n<p>Slug Bicycles started as a made-to-order Taiwanese frame company, helping customers dial in a custom titanium bike that suits their needs. For an emblematic example, we looked at <a href=\"https://theradavist.com/slug-bicycles-review-gasser-rigid-titanium-29er/\" target=\"_blank\">Alex’s Slug back in 2022</a>. At the core of this rebrand and release for 2025 is the brand’s first production hardtail, the Gasser.</p>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/02/Slug_Bicycles_2025-Gasser_Hardtail_04.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/02/Slug_Bicycles_2025-Gasser_Hardtail_04.jpg?w=650&amp;quality=75 640w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/02/Slug_Bicycles_2025-Gasser_Hardtail_04.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75 1800w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/02/Slug_Bicycles_2025-Gasser_Hardtail_04.jpg?w=2000&amp;quality=75\" /></p>\n<h3><a href=\"https://slugbicycles.com/products/gasser-hardtail-mountain-bike\" target=\"_blank\">Gasser Hardtail Mountain Bike</a></h3>\n<p>The Gasser is Slug’s 120 – 130 mm travel hardtail. It clears a 29 x 2.6″ tire, has a 3D printed yoke, and is available for pre-order today. Retail for the frame is $2700, or a complete build with Shimano XT rolls in at $5600 for a RockShox Sid fork and OneUp dropper.</p>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/02/Slug_Bicycles_2025-Gasser_Hardtail_02.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/02/Slug_Bicycles_2025-Gasser_Hardtail_02.jpg?w=400&amp;quality=75 800w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/02/Slug_Bicycles_2025-Gasser_Hardtail_02.jpg?w=1000&amp;quality=75 1600w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/02/Slug_Bicycles_2025-Gasser_Hardtail_02.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75\" /><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/02/Slug_Bicycles_2025-Gasser_Hardtail_03.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/02/Slug_Bicycles_2025-Gasser_Hardtail_03.jpg?w=400&amp;quality=75 800w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/02/Slug_Bicycles_2025-Gasser_Hardtail_03.jpg?w=1000&amp;quality=75 1600w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/02/Slug_Bicycles_2025-Gasser_Hardtail_03.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75\" /></p>\n<h3>Gasser Hardtail Quick Hits:</h3>\n<ul>\n<li>Sizes: S-XXL</li>\n<li>Fork Compatibility: 120mm – 130mm</li>\n<li>BB Shell: 73mm Threaded T47</li>\n<li>Max Tire: 29 x 2.6″</li>\n<li>Premium 3Al-2.5V Titanium</li>\n<li>3D-printed (SLM) Titanium yoke, designed in-house</li>\n<li>Universal Derailleur Hanger. DUH!</li>\n<li>Proudly Made in Taiwan</li>\n<li>MSRP: $2700</li>\n</ul>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/02/Slug_Gasser_Hardtail_Geo.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/02/Slug_Gasser_Hardtail_Geo.jpg?w=650&amp;quality=75 640w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/02/Slug_Gasser_Hardtail_Geo.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75 1800w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/02/Slug_Gasser_Hardtail_Geo.jpg?w=2000&amp;quality=75\" /></p>\n<h3>Gasser Geometry</h3>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/02/slug-bicycles-Terrestrial-ti-Bar-2.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/02/slug-bicycles-Terrestrial-ti-Bar-2.jpg?w=650&amp;quality=75 640w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/02/slug-bicycles-Terrestrial-ti-Bar-2.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75 1800w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/02/slug-bicycles-Terrestrial-ti-Bar-2.jpg?w=2000&amp;quality=75\" /></p>\n<h3><a href=\"https://slugbicycles.com/products/terrestrial-ti-handlebars\" target=\"_blank\">Terrestrial Ti Bars</a></h3>\n<p>Along with the Gasser, Slug announced its Terrestrial Ti handlebars. Designed in two configurations, 0 or 25 mm rise, with 13º backsweep, these 31.8 clamp bars are perfect for a hardtail or rigid tourer and offer damping qualities titanium is known for.</p>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/02/slug-bicycles-Terrestrial-ti-Bar-1.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/02/slug-bicycles-Terrestrial-ti-Bar-1.jpg?w=650&amp;quality=75 640w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/02/slug-bicycles-Terrestrial-ti-Bar-1.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75 1800w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/02/slug-bicycles-Terrestrial-ti-Bar-1.jpg?w=2000&amp;quality=75\" /></p>\n<h3>Terrestrial Ti Bars Quick Hits</h3>\n<ul>\n<li>0 mm or 25 mm rise</li>\n<li>13-degree back sweep</li>\n<li>780 mm wide</li>\n<li>31.8 clamp diameter</li>\n<li>Proudly Made in Taiwan</li>\n<li>MSRP: $265</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Check it all out at <a href=\"https://slugbicycles.com/\" target=\"_blank\">Slug Bicycles</a>.</p>\n<p>The post <a href=\"https://theradavist.com/slug-bicycles-gasser-hardtail-terrestrial-ti-bars/\">Slug Bicycles Returns with Gasser Hardtail and Terrestrial Ti Bars</a> appeared first on <a href=\"https://theradavist.com\">The Radavist</a>.</p>","author":"John Watson","siteTitle":"The Radavist","siteHash":"96eb481d8084f04a4602bac57874ba717baf56b758f45547b5caf2312da766ef","entryHash":"9c503b52dab60e7124ddf79f98683fdde08ed94e8428c2379acde0ed3a565c08","category":"Cycling"}